{"title_page": "Chavannes Jeune", "text_new": "'''Chavannes Jeune''' is an influential [[Haiti]]an [[christianity|Christian]] leader, pastor and evangelist, and an unsuccessful candidate for [[President of Haiti]] in 2005.\n\nBorn in Haiti on December 29, 1953, Pastor Chavannes grew up in an evangelistic household; his father was a pioneer of the [[Evangelical Baptist Mission of South Haiti|Mission Evangelique Baptiste du Sud d'Haiti]] (MEBSH). During a [[Vacation Bible School]] at age seven Chavannes made his own personal commitment to Christ, followed by baptism at fourteen. Although Chavannes graduated with a degree as a [[civil engineering|civil engineer]], he knew his real mission in life lay not in building an earthly city, but in furthering a Heavenly Kingdom. He announced his candidacy for president in his home town of [[Les Cayes]] on Wednesday, August 10, 2005. He is one of the advisor of Haiti's President Joseph Michel Martelly.\n\n==References==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20060427052442/http://www.newdirections.org/partnershipsview.php?id=7 Biography]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20060822174131/http://headlines.agapepress.org/archive/8/112006f.asp Can Believers Help Haiti Move From Curse Into Hope?, Agape Press, Feature by Jean R. Gelin, PhD, August 11, 2006]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20060512212246/http://www.lincolntribune.com/modules/news/article.php?storyid=1977 Evangelical Leader to Seek Haitian Presidency, Lincoln Tribune, By Michael Barrick, August 6, 2005]\n*[[Elections in Haiti]]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Jeune, Chavannes}}\n[[Category:1953 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Haitian Baptists]]\n[[Category:Haitian religious leaders]]\n[[Category:Candidates for President of Haiti]]\n\n\n{{Haiti-politician-stub}}\n", "text_old": "'''Chavannes Jeune''' is an influential [[Haiti]]an [[christianity|Christian]] leader, pastor and evangelist, and an unsuccessful candidate for [[President of Haiti]] in 2005.\n\nBorn in Haiti on December 29, 1953, Pastor Chavannes grew up in an evangelistic household; his father was a pioneer of the [[Evangelical Baptist Mission of South Haiti|Mission Evangelique Baptiste du Sud d'Haiti]] (MEBSH). During a [[Vacation Bible School]] at age seven Chavannes made his own personal commitment to Christ, followed by baptism at fourteen. Although Chavannes graduated with a degree as a [[civil engineering|civil engineer]], he knew his real mission in life lay not in building an earthly city, but in furthering a Heavenly Kingdom. He announced his candidacy for President in his home town of [[Les Cayes]] on Wednesday, August 10, 2005. He is one of the advisor of Haiti's President Joseph Michel Martelly.\n\n==References==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20060427052442/http://www.newdirections.org/partnershipsview.php?id=7 Biography]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20060822174131/http://headlines.agapepress.org/archive/8/112006f.asp Can Believers Help Haiti Move From Curse Into Hope?, Agape Press, Feature by Jean R. Gelin, PhD, August 11, 2006]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20060512212246/http://www.lincolntribune.com/modules/news/article.php?storyid=1977 Evangelical Leader to Seek Haitian Presidency, Lincoln Tribune, By Michael Barrick, August 6, 2005]\n*[[Elections in Haiti]]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Jeune, Chavannes}}\n[[Category:1953 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Haitian Baptists]]\n[[Category:Haitian religious leaders]]\n[[Category:Candidates for President of Haiti]]\n\n\n{{Haiti-politician-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Chris the speller", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:typo(s) fixed: President \u2192 president", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chavannes_Jeune"}
{"title_page": "Netsky (musician)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2018}}\n{{Infobox musical artist <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Musicians -->\n| name             = Netsky\n| image            = Netsky (DJ) 2008.jpg\n| caption          = Netsky in 2008\n| landscape        = yes\n| background       = non_vocal_instrumentalist\n| birth_name       = Boris Daenen\n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1989|3|22}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/netskymusic |title=Netsky's Twitter}}</ref>\n| birth_place      = [[Edegem]], Belgium\n| instrument       = \n| genre            = {{hlist|[[Drum and bass]]|[[liquid funk]]|[[drumstep]]|[[Trap music (EDM)|trap]]|[[house music|house]]|[[electro house]]}}\n| occupation       = {{hlist|Record producer|DJ|keyboardist|bandleader}}\n| years_active     = 2008\u2013present\n| label            = {{hlist|[[Hospital Records|Hospital]] {{small|(2009\u201314)}} {{small|(2020-present)}}|[[Sony Music|Sony]] {{small|(2014\u20132019)}}}}|[[Hospital Records|Hospital]] {{small|(2020-present)}}\n| website          = {{url|netskymusic.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Boris Daenen''' ({{IPA-nl|\u02c8bo\u02d0r\u026as \u02c8da\u02d0n\u0259(n)|lang}}; born 22 March 1989), better known by his stage name '''Netsky''' ({{IPAc-en|'|n|\u025b|t|.|s|k|a\u026a}} {{respell|net|SKY}}),<ref>{{cite web|title=[Hypeon.Tv] - Netsky - Beach Break Live 2012 Interview|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uIxlwCu8878|accessdate=29 December 2018}} ''Event occurs at 0:21''</ref> is a Belgian [[drum and bass]] producer and musician.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://drumandbass.me.uk/home/item/52-netsky-with-contract |title=Netsky with contract |publisher=Drum And Bass |accessdate=12 March 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100819194633/http://drumandbass.me.uk/home/item/52-netsky-with-contract/ |archivedate=19 August 2010 }}</ref> The name Netsky is based on the [[Netsky (computer worm)|computer virus of the same name]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zRi6ElbddoU |title=Netsky Interview |publisher=YouTube |date= |accessdate=12 March 2011}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nNetsky produces music of the [[liquid funk]] style \u2013 drum and bass music with many instrumental layers and frequent vocals.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://examplemagazine.com/features/post/202/10-Essential-Drum-&-Bass-Artists-for-2010-Part-1 |title=Features \" Issue 15 \" 10 Essential Drum & Bass Artists for 2010 Part 1 |publisher=Example Magazine |accessdate=12 March 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101214113431/http://examplemagazine.com/features/post/202/10-Essential-Drum-%26-Bass-Artists-for-2010-Part-1 |archivedate=14 December 2010 }}</ref> High Contrast's 'Gold Digger' remix was a major influence on him.\n\nIn late 2009, Netsky signed a recording contract with [[Hospital Records]], the same label as other well known liquid artists such as [[High Contrast]] and [[London Elektricity]]. He also won a nomination as \"Best Upcoming Producer\" within just months of his first release at the Drum + Bass Arena Awards.{{fact|date=June 2019}}\n\nHospital Records released Netsky's self-titled debut album on 31 May 2010. His second album, titled ''2'', was released on 25 June 2012.<ref>Hospital Podcast 109. Netsky's second feature length album was released at the end of June 2012, on Hospital Records.</ref> The album features three singles and a deluxe edition was later released supported by a fourth single, \"[[We Can Only Live Today (Puppy)]]\".{{fact|date=June 2019}}\n\nHis 2015 single \"Rio\" featured in the London 2016 New Year's celebrations.{{fact|date=June 2019}}\n\n==Netsky Live! project==\nIn April 2012, during a [[Hospital Records#Hospitality|Hospitality]] festival at [[Brixton Academy]], Netsky unveiled his \"Netsky LIVE!\" project for the first time.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CrHT8RlMC2Q |title=Netsky LIVE! Hospitality at Brixton Academy 6th April 2012}}</ref> Accompanied by a team of live musicians, as well as guest vocalists (of whom have sung on Netsky's catalogue of music), Netsky performs his music as a full band, taking center-stage on keyboards and synthesizers. The band now tours the world performing headlining shows around the globe, as well as performing at many international electronic music festivals, such as the [[Ultra Music Festival]] in the [[United States]].\n\n;Netsky Live! members\n*Netsky - [[MIDI keyboard|Keyboards]], [[Synthesizer|synths]], [[bandleader]] <small>(2012\u2013present)</small>\n*BABL - Keyboards, synths <small>(2012\u2013present)</small>\n*Michael Schack - [[Drum kit|Drums]] <small>(2012\u2013present)</small>\n*Script MC - [[Master of ceremonies|MC]] <small>(2012\u2013present)</small>\n*[[Diane Charlemagne]] - [[Singing|Vocals]] <small>(2012-2015\u2020)</small>\n*Billie - Vocals <small>(2012\u2013present)</small>\n\n==Discography==\n===Studio albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:30em;\"| Details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"3\"| Chart positions\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Ultratop|BEL (FL)]]<br><ref name=belfl>{{cite web|url=http://www.ultratop.be/nl/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Netsky|title=Belgium (Flanders) Charts > Netsky|language=Dutch|publisher=ultratop.be/nl Hung Medien}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Official New Zealand Music Chart|NZ]]<br><ref name=nz>{{cite web|url=https://charts.nz/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Netsky|title=New Zealand Charts > Netsky|publisher=charts.nz/ Hung Medien}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[UK Singles Chart|UK]]<br><ref name=uk>Peak positions for albums & singles in the United Kingdom:\n* For all except where noted: {{cite web|url=http://www.theofficialcharts.com/artist/_/netsky|title=The Official Charts Company \u2013 Netsky (musician)|date=5 May 2013|publisher=The Official Charts Company}}\n* For \"Give & Take\": {{cite web|url=http://www.zobbel.de/cluk/120128cluk.txt|title=New Chart Entries > January 28, 2012|publisher=Zobbel.de|date=28 January 2012}}\n* For \"Come Alive\": {{cite web|url=http://www.zobbel.de/cluk/120602cluk.txt|title=New Chart Entries > June 2, 2012|publisher=Zobbel.de|date=2 June 2012}}\n* For \"Love Has Gone\": {{cite web|url=http://www.zobbel.de/cluk/120707cluk.txt|title=New Chart Entries > July 7, 2012|publisher=Zobbel.de|date=7 July 2012}}\n* For \"Rio\": {{cite web|url=http://www.zobbel.de/cluk/150926cluk.txt|title=New Chart Entries > September 26, 2015|publisher=Zobbel.de|date=26 September 2015}}\n* For \"Work It Out\": {{cite web|url=http://www.zobbel.de/cluk/160130cluk.txt|title=New Chart Entries > January 30, 2016|publisher=Zobbel.de|date=30 January 2016}}\n</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Netsky (album)|Netsky]]''\n|\n* Released: 30 May 2010\n* Label: [[Hospital Records]] <small>(NHS167)</small>\n* Format: [[LP record|LP]], [[compact disc|CD]], [[music download|download]]\n| 24 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[2 (Netsky album)|2]]''\n|\n* Released: 25 June 2012\n* Label: Hospital Records <small>(NHS213)</small>\n* Format: LP, CD, download\n| 1 || 13 || 29\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[3 (Netsky album)|3]]''\n|\n* Released: 3 June 2016\n* Label: Hospital Records <small>(NHS289)</small>, Sony / Epic <small>(UK)</small>, Ultra <small>(US)</small>\n* Format: LP, CD, download\n| 1 || 25 || 109\n|}\n\n===Extended plays===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of extended plays\n! scope=\"col\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" | Details\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Abbot Kinney''<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://dancingastronaut.com/2018/12/netsky-thrills-end-year-abbot-kinney-ep/ |title=Netsky thrills with end-of-year ''Abbot Kinney'' EP |last=Dexter |first=Robyn |date=15 December 2018 |website=[[Dancing Astronaut]] |archive-ur