eleases-invigorating-remix-pack-dont-even-know-anymore/ |archive-date=20 March 2019 |accessdate=20 March 2019}}</ref>\n| ''I Don't Even Know You Anymore (Remixes)''\n|}\n{{reflist|group=lower-alpha}}\n\n===Other releases===\n;2009\n* Crystal Clear & Netsky \u2013 \"King of the Stars\" [Liq-weed Ganja Recordings]\n* Netsky \u2013 \"Starlight\" / \"Young and Foolish\" [Allsorts]\n* Netsky \u2013 \"Lost in This World\" <small>(b/w \"Life\" by KG)</small> [Talkin Beatz]\n* Netsky \u2013 \"Prisma\" / \"Tomorrow's Another Day\" [Liq-weed Ganja Recordings]\n* Netsky \u2013 \"Hold on to Love\" <small>(b/w \"Generations ([[S.P.Y]] Remix)\" by BCee)</small> [Future Retro]\n* Netsky \u2013 \"Everyday\" / \"Come Back Home\" [Liq-weed Ganja Recordings]\n\n;2010\n* Netsky \u2013 \"I Refuse\" / \"Midnight Express\" [Spearhead Records]\n* Netsky \u2013 \"Eyes Closed\" / \"Smile\" [Allsorts]\n* Netsky \u2013 \"I Refuse (Shock One Remix)\" / \"Hold on To Love (Cyantific Remix)\" [Spearhead Records]\n* Netsky \u2013 \"Your Way\" / \"Daydreaming\" [Radar Records]\n* Mutated Forms & Netsky featuring Sofia Rubina \u2013 \"Windows\" [Allsorts]\n\n===Guest appearances===\n;2009\n* ''Strength in Numbers EP'' (by Crystal Clear) \u2013 Netsky \u2013 \"Come Back Home\" [Frontline Records]\n\n;2010\n* ''Hospital Mix.Eight'' (mixed by Logistics) \u2013 Netsky \u2013 \"Memory Lane\" [Hospital Records]\n* ''This is Drum + Bass'' (presented by Hospitality) \u2013 Netsky \u2013 \"Smile\" [Hospital Records]\n* ''Sick Music 2'' \u2013 Netsky \u2013 \"Memory Lane\" [Hospital Records]\n* ''Drum & Bass Arena Anthology'' \u2013 Netsky \u2013 \"I Refuse\" [Hospital Records]\n\n;2011\n* ''Fifteen Years of Hospital Records'' \u2013 Netsky \u2013 \"Secret Agent\" [Hospital Records]\n\n;2014\n* ''Hospital: We Are 18'' \u2013 Netsky \u2013 \"Love Life\" [Hospital Records]\n\n;2015\n* ''Fast Soul Music'' \u2013 Netsky \u2013 \"Memory Lane\" [Hospital Records]\n\n==References==\n===Notes===\n{{notelist-ua}}\n\n===Sources===\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Netsky}}\n* {{Official website|http://netskymusic.com}}\n\n{{Netsky}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Netsky}}\n[[Category:1989 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Belgian dance musicians]]\n[[Category:Belgian DJs]]\n[[Category:Hospital Records artists]]\n[[Category:Drum and bass musicians]]\n[[Category:People from Edegem]]\n[[Category:Electronic dance music DJs]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2018}}\n{{Infobox musical artist <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Musicians -->\n| name             = Netsky\n| image            = Netsky (DJ) 2008.jpg\n| caption          = Netsky in 2008\n| landscape        = yes\n| background       = non_vocal_instrumentalist\n| birth_name       = Boris Daenen\n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1989|3|22}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/netskymusic |title=Netsky's Twitter}}</ref>\n| birth_place      = [[Edegem]], Belgium\n| instrument       = \n| genre            = {{hlist|[[Drum and bass]]|[[liquid funk]]|[[drumstep]]|[[Trap music (EDM)|trap]]|[[house music|house]]|[[electro house]]}}\n| occupation       = {{hlist|Record producer|DJ|keyboardist|bandleader}}\n| years_active     = 2008\u2013present\n| label            = {{hlist|[[Hospital Records|Hospital]] {{small|(2009\u201314)}} {{small|(2020-present)}}|[[Sony Music|Sony]] {{small|(2014\u20132019)}}}}|[[Hospital Records|Hospital]] {{small|(2020-present)}}\n| website          = {{url|netskymusic.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Boris Daenen''' ({{IPA-nl|\u02c8bo\u02d0r\u026as \u02c8da\u02d0n\u0259(n)|lang}}; born 22 March 1989), better known by his stage name '''Netsky''' ({{IPAc-en|'|n|\u025b|t|.|s|k|a\u026a}} {{respell|net|SKY}}),<ref>{{cite web|title=[Hypeon.Tv] - Netsky - Beach Break Live 2012 Interview|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uIxlwCu8878|accessdate=29 December 2018}} ''Event occurs at 0:21''</ref> is a Belgian [[drum and bass]] producer and musician.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://drumandbass.me.uk/home/item/52-netsky-with-contract |title=Netsky with contract |publisher=Drum And Bass |accessdate=12 March 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100819194633/http://drumandbass.me.uk/home/item/52-netsky-with-contract/ |archivedate=19 August 2010 }}</ref> The name Netsky is based on the [[Netsky (computer worm)|computer virus of the same name]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zRi6ElbddoU |title=Netsky Interview |publisher=YouTube |date= |accessdate=12 March 2011}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nNetsky produces music of the [[liquid funk]] style \u2013 drum and bass music with many instrumental layers and frequent vocals.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://examplemagazine.com/features/post/202/10-Essential-Drum-&-Bass-Artists-for-2010-Part-1 |title=Features \" Issue 15 \" 10 Essential Drum & Bass Artists for 2010 Part 1 |publisher=Example Magazine |accessdate=12 March 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101214113431/http://examplemagazine.com/features/post/202/10-Essential-Drum-%26-Bass-Artists-for-2010-Part-1 |archivedate=14 December 2010 }}</ref> High Contrast's 'Gold Digger' remix was a major influence on him.\n\nIn late 2009, Netsky signed a recording contract with [[Hospital Records]], the same label as other well known liquid artists such as [[High Contrast]] and [[London Elektricity]]. He also won a nomination as \"Best Upcoming Producer\" within just months of his first release at the Drum + Bass Arena Awards.{{fact|date=June 2019}}\n\nHospital Records released Netsky's self-titled debut album on 31 May 2010. His second album, titled ''2'', was released on 25 June 2012.<ref>Hospital Podcast 109. Netsky's second feature length album was released at the end of June 2012, on Hospital Records.</ref> The album features three singles and a deluxe edition was later released supported by a fourth single, \"[[We Can Only Live Today (Puppy)]]\".{{fact|date=June 2019}}\n\nHis 2015 single \"Rio\" featured in the London 2016 New Year's celebrations.{{fact|date=June 2019}}\n\n==Netsky Live! project==\nIn April 2012, during a [[Hospital Records#Hospitality|Hospitality]] festival at [[Brixton Academy]], Netsky unveiled his \"Netsky LIVE!\" project for the first time.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CrHT8RlMC2Q |title=Netsky LIVE! Hospitality at Brixton Academy 6th April 2012}}</ref> Accompanied by a team of live musicians, as well as guest vocalists (of whom have sung on Netsky's catalogue of music), Netsky performs his music as a full band, taking center-stage on keyboards and synthesizers. The band now tours the world performing headlining shows around the globe, as well as performing at many international electronic music festivals, such as the [[Ultra Music Festival]] in the [[United States]].\n\n;Netsky Live! members\n*Netsky - [[MIDI keyboard|Keyboards]], [[Synthesizer|synths]], [[bandleader]] <small>(2012\u2013present)</small>\n*BABL - Keyboards, synths <small>(2012\u2013present)</small>\n*Michael Schack - [[Drum kit|Drums]] <small>(2012\u2013present)</small>\n*Script MC - [[Master of ceremonies|MC]] <small>(2012\u2013present)</small>\n*[[Diane Charlemagne]] - [[Singing|Vocals]] <small>(2012-2015\u2020)</small>\n*Billie - Vocals <small>(2012\u2013present)</small>\n\n==Discography==\n===Studio albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:30em;\"| Details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"3\"| Chart positions\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Ultratop|BEL (FL)]]<br><ref name=belfl>{{cite web|url=http://www.ultratop.be/nl/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Netsky|title=Belgium (Flanders) Charts > Netsky|language=Dutch|publisher=ultratop.be/nl Hung Medien}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Official New Zealand Music Chart|NZ]]<br><ref name=nz>{{cite web|u